<exercise checkit-seed="0002" checkit-slug="P6" checkit-title="Probability with Advanced Counting">
    <statement>
        <p>
            
            
            
            
            
                <ol>
                    <li>From a pool of 37 candidates, 6 people will be selected at random to go on an expedition. They will all be assigned unique tasks. You and 10 of your friends are all in the pool of candidates. What is the probability that a team is selected that  consists only of you and your friends?</li>
                    <li>When drawing a 5 card hand from a standard 52 card poker deck, what is the probability that you draw two Twos?</li>
                </ol>
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            
            
            
            
            
                <ol>
                    <li>The probability is <m>\frac{\,_{11}P_{6}}{\,_{37}P_{6}} = 0.0001987281399046105</m></li>
                    <li>The probability is <m>\frac{(\,_{4}C_2)(\,_{48}C_3)}{\,_{52}C_5} = \frac{2162}{54145}</m></li>
                </ol>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
